YENAGOA – The All Progressives Con­gress (APC) in Bayelsa State said that it will on Thurs­day, May 5, play host to Vice President Yemi Osinbajo in Yenagoa, the state capital. The state APC Publicity Secretary, Doifie Buokoribo, announced this in a state­ment he issued on Wednesday. He said that Osinbajo, a presidential aspirant on the platform of the APC, will meet with members of the party in the state as part of preparations for the party’s forthcoming 2023 primary election scheduled for the end of May. -Advertisement- According to him, the vice president will also visit the secretariat of the state Tra­ditional Rulers Council for a parley with members of the council. Buokoribo said that Osin­bajo will thereafter proceed to the state secretariat of the party on Mbiama-Yenagoa Road for a meeting with the state executive committee. He further stated that the presidential aspirant will round off his visit to Bayelsa with a meeting with all na­tional delegates of the state chapter of APC at the Gold­en Tulip Hotel, Government House, Yenagoa.